 {"id":"flywheel_connectors-62ai5","title":"[MOR/C3.4] Make capability constraints mandatory; reject null/empty constraints","status":"closed","priority":0,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-08T03:34:57.050666Z","created_by":"jemanuel","updated_at":"2026-04-10T23:50:57.007185Z","closed_at":"2026-04-10T23:50:57.006485Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["P0-critical","capability","security"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"flywheel_connectors-62ai5","depends_on_id":"flywheel_connectors-800e3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-04-08T03:37:41.067762Z","created_by":"jemanuel","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"flywheel_connectors-62ai5","depends_on_id":"flywheel_connectors-8whb3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-04-08T03:37:06.752983Z","created_by":"jemanuel","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"flywheel_connectors-62ai5","depends_on_id":"flywheel_connectors-ky3yv","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-04-08T03:37:09.737664Z","created_by":"jemanuel","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":2643,"issue_id":"flywheel_connectors-62ai5","author":"jemanuel","text":"WHAT: Make capability constraints mandatory in CapabilityToken. Reject tokens with null/empty/missing constraints. Define a DENY-ALL default when constraints are absent (empty resource list = no operations allowed). WHY: H2 Adversarial found capability ceiling constraint bypass (#9, HIGH): if constraints are None, enforce_resource_constraints() is never called. An attacker-controlled issuer can issue unconstrained capabilities to arbitrary resources. J1 Deontic found this violates the default-deny principle — a null constraint should mean no access, not unlimited access. WHERE: crates/fcp-core/src/capability.rs — CapabilityToken verification path, specifically the constraint enforcement section. Change: if constraints is None, return Err(FcpError::CapabilityDenied) instead of skipping. Also update CapabilityToken construction to require constraints. 