 {"id":"flywheel_connectors-9seey","title":"[REVIEW-A9-FUZZ][P2] fcp-protocol/symbol_envelope.rs: missing fuzz target for decrypt_symbol + derive_sender_subkey","description":"crates/fcp-protocol/src/symbol_envelope.rs has no fuzz target. fuzz/fuzz_targets/ already covers FCPS frames (fcps_frame.rs, fcps_datagram.rs, mesh_post_verify_*) but the per-symbol AEAD layer that those frames carry is uncovered.

fuzzable inputs (one or two harnesses):

1. decrypt_symbol(zone_key, algorithm, ctx, ciphertext, auth_tag):
   - Arbitrary `ciphertext: &[u8]` (cap to e.g. 64 KiB to keep exec rate)
   - Arbitrary `auth_tag: [u8; AUTH_TAG_SIZE]`
   - Derived SymbolContext fields {object_id, esi, k, zone_id_hash, zone_key_id, epoch_id, sender_node_id, sender_instance_id} from `Arbitrary`
   - Algorithm switch over ZoneKeyAlgorithm (ChaCha20Poly1305 + XChaCha20Poly1305)
   - Property: never panic, never decrypt successfully (random ciphertext should fail AEAD); tag mismatch must surface as InvalidTag

2. derive_sender_subkey(zone_key, zone_key_id, sender_node_id, sender_instance_id):
   - Arbitrary TailscaleNodeId string (use try_new path so canonicalization caps apply)
   - Property: HKDF expansion never panics on the 32-byte output (the existing .expect() at line 121-123 should hold); equal inputs derive equal subkeys

3. build_symbol_aad(ctx) and derive_nonce12 / derive_nonce24:
   - Pure byte-layout functions; fuzz mostly for compile-time determinism but worth checking that consecutive calls with same inputs produce byte-identical outputs (anti-regression on layout drift)

reproduction shell:
  cargo +nightly fuzz run symbol_envelope_decrypt -- -max_total_time=60
  cargo +nightly fuzz run symbol_envelope_derive_sender_subkey -- -max_total_time=60

